<h1>About</h1>
<p>
	<em>'afterwritings labs</em>&nbsp;is a place where you can play around with some tools for screenplays. You can use screenplays written in <a href="http://fountain.io/" target="_blank"><strong>Fountain format</strong></a> or <a href="http://www.finaldraft.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Final Draft</strong></a> (itl will be converted to fountain). You can aske use one of the
	<a class="switch" href="#" plugin="open">samples</a>.</p>
<p>You can use it offline as well (sorry, no Dropbox support for offline version). Just download this
	<a href="afterwriting.zip" id="download-link">file</a>, unzip and double click on afterwriting.html.</p>
<p>
	<em>Warning: this product may contain nuts and bugs!</em>
</p>
<h1>What's inside?</h1>
<p>Available plugins:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		<img src="{{static_path}}gfx/icons/open.svg" />&nbsp;/&nbsp;
		<img src="gfx/icons/save.svg" />&nbsp;
		<em>Open / Save</em>&nbsp;- open a .fountain file from disk, Dropbox or use a sample, save as .fountain or as PDF.</li>
	<li>
		<img src="{{static_path}}gfx/icons/settings.svg" />
		<em>Settings</em>&nbsp;- change paper size, print layout, etc.</li>
	<li>
		<img src="{{static_path}}gfx/icons/editor.svg" />
		<em>Editor</em>&nbsp;- a basic editor for
		<a href="http://fountain.io/" target="_blank">.fountain files</a>
	</li>
	<li>
		<img src="{{static_path}}gfx/icons/preview.svg" />
		<em>Preview</em>&nbsp;- PDF preview (a browser plugin required)</li>
	<li>
		<img src="{{static_path}}gfx/icons/facts.svg" />
		<em>Facts</em>&nbsp;- facts about your screenplay (number of pages, scenes, characters, etc.)</li>
	<li>
		<img src="{{static_path}}gfx/icons/stats.svg" />
		<em>Useless Stats</em>&nbsp;- some statistics, don't take them too seriously!</li>
</ul>
